ision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(80,1,'2020-06-29 12:58:32','2020-06-29 15:58:32','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://g1.globo.com/tudo-sobre/ans/\">Agência Nacional de Saúde Suplementar</a>&nbsp;(ANS) incluiu nesta segunda-feira (29) o teste sorológico para o novo coronavírus na lista de coberturas obrigatórias dos planos de saúde. A medida foi publicada hoje no Diário Oficial da União e passa a valer imediatamente.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A inclusão do teste teste sorológico no Rol de Procedimentos e Eventos em Saúde atende à decisão judicial dada em Ação Civil Pública e pode ser feito sem custo extra, contando que haja requisição feita por um médico.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A mudança era ensaiada desde março pelo Ministério da Saúde. Naquela ocasião, o então secretário-executivo do Ministério da Saúde, João Gabbardo dos Reis, disse que&nbsp;<a href=\"https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/10/teste-para-coronavirus-sera-incluido-na-lista-de-cobertura-obrigatoria-dos-planos-de-saude.ghtml\">os planos poderiam cobrar pelo teste pois o procedimento não estava no rol de cobertura obrigatória</a>, mas que as empresas seriam obrigadas a bancar os testes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','ANS define teste sorológico para o novo coronavírus como cobertura obrigatória de planos de saúde','','publish','open','open','','ans-define-teste-sorologico-para-o-novo-coronavirus-como-cobertura-obrigatoria-de-planos-de-saude','','','2020-06-30 11:05:42','2020-06-30 14:05:42','',0,'http://localhost/?p=80',0,'post','',0),(81,1,'2020-06-29 12:58:14','2020-06-29 15:58:14','','','','inherit','open','closed','','sangue','','','2020-06-30 11:05:03','2020-06-30 14:05:03','',80,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/sangue.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(82,1,'2020-06-29 12:58:32','2020-06-29 15:58:32','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A&nbsp;<a href=\"https://g1.globo.com/tudo-sobre/ans/\">Agência Nacional de Saúde Suplementar</a>&nbsp;(ANS) incluiu nesta segunda-feira (29) o teste sorológico para o novo coronavírus na lista de coberturas obrigatórias dos planos de saúde. A medida foi publicada hoje no Diário Oficial da União e passa a valer imediatamente.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A inclusão do teste teste sorológico no Rol de Procedimentos e Eventos em Saúde atende à decisão judicial dada em Ação Civil Pública e pode ser feito sem custo extra, contando que haja requisição feita por um médico.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A mudança era ensaiada desde março pelo Ministério da Saúde. Naquela ocasião, o então secretário-executivo do Ministério da Saúde, João Gabbardo dos Reis, disse que&nbsp;<a href=\"https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/10/teste-para-coronavirus-sera-incluido-na-lista-de-cobertura-obrigatoria-dos-planos-de-saude.ghtml\">os planos poderiam cobrar pelo teste pois o procedimento não estava no rol de cobertura obrigatória</a>, mas que as empresas seriam obrigadas a bancar os testes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','ANS define teste sorológico para o novo coronavírus como cobertura obrigatória de planos de saúde','','inherit','closed','closed','','80-revision-v1','','','2020-06-29 12:58:32','2020-06-29 15:58:32','',80,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/29/80-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(83,1,'2020-06-29 13:00:09','2020-06-29 16:00:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Manifestantes ocupam nesta segunda-feira (29) duas faixas da avenida Afonso Pena, no Centro de Belo Horizonte, para protestar contra o fechamento do comércio. O encontro começou às 10h na porta da prefeitura da capital.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Entre as reivindicações estão a reabertura de bares, restaurantes, academias e shoppings. A Polícia Militar e a Empresa de Transporte e Trânsito de Belo Horizonte (BHTrans) estão no local monitorando o trânsito.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Manifestantes pedem reabertura do comércio em Belo Horizonte','','publish','open','open','','manifestantes-pedem-reabertura-do-comercio-em-belo-horizonte','','','2020-06-30 11:06:37','2020-06-30 14:06:37','',0,'http://localhost/?p=83',0,'post','',0),(84,1,'2020-06-29 12:59:44','2020-06-29 15:59:44','','','','inherit','open','closed','','caixao-em-protesto','','','2020-06-30 11:05:44','2020-06-30 14:05:44','',83,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/caixao-em-protesto.jpeg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(85,1,'2020-06-29 13:00:09','2020-06-29 16:00:09','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Manifestantes ocupam nesta segunda-feira (29) duas faixas da avenida Afonso Pena, no Centro de Belo Horizonte, para protestar contra o fechamento do comércio. O encontro começou às 10h na porta da prefeitura da capital.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Entre as reivindicações estão a reabertura de bares, restaurantes, academias e shoppings. A Polícia Militar e a Empresa de Transporte e Trânsito de Belo Horizonte (BHTrans) estão no local monitorando o trânsito.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Manifestantes pedem reabertura do comércio em Belo Horizonte','','inherit','closed','closed','','83-revision-v1','','','2020-06-29 13:00:09','2020-06-29 16:00:09','',83,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/29/83-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(87,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:05','2020-06-29 16:02:05','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“It fully reflects the active engagement of Cambodia in the MLC and demonstrates that the China-Cambodia cooperation within the MLC is highly fruitful. We hope the projects will help improve Cambodian people’s livelihoods and speed up Cambodia’s development in economy, society and other areas,” he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“The application of 2021 project is now under way. We expect an early confirmation of a new round of quality projects, which will provide more support for economic and social development of the region after the COVID-19 pandemic. China would like to work with Cambodia as well as other Lancang-Mekong River countries to implement the MLC Special Fund Projects,” Mr Wang added.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr Sokhonn said that in February last year, Cambodia implemented the second batch of projects supported by the MLC Special Fund 2018.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Since the launch of the MLC Special Fund in 2016, these projects have contributed to enhancing the socio-economic development of the Mekong-Lancang countries through narrowing development gaps, deepening mutual understanding and trust and strengthening our capacity to better respond to the needs of our peoples,” he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Cambodia the biggest beneficiary of MLC Special Fund projects','','publish','open','open','','cambodia-the-biggest-beneficiary-of-mlc-special-fund-projects','','','2020-06-29 13:03:14','2020-06-29 16:03:14','',0,'http://localhost/?p=87',0,'post','',0),(88,1,'2020-06-29 13:01:47','2020-06-29 16:01:47','','','','inherit','open','closed','','4342','','','2020-06-30 11:12:05','2020-06-30 14:12:05','',87,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/4342.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(89,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:05','2020-06-29 16:02:05','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“It fully reflects the active engagement of Cambodia in the MLC and demonstrates that the China-Cambodia cooperation within the MLC is highly fruitful. We hope the projects will help improve Cambodian people’s livelihoods and speed up Cambodia’s development in economy, society and other areas,” he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“The application of 2021 project is now under way. We expect an early confirmation of a new round of quality projects, which will provide more support for economic and social development of the region after the COVID-19 pandemic. China would like to work with Cambodia as well as other Lancang-Mekong River countries to implement the MLC Special Fund Projects,” Mr Wang added.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mr Sokhonn said that in February last year, Cambodia implemented the second batch of projects supported by the MLC Special Fund 2018.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>“Since the launch of the MLC Special Fund in 2016, these projects have contributed to enhancing the socio-economic development of the Mekong-Lancang countries through narrowing development gaps, deepening mutual understanding and trust and strengthening our capacity to better respond to the needs of our peoples,” he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Cambodia the biggest beneficiary of MLC Special Fund projects','','inherit','closed','closed','','87-revision-v1','','','2020-06-29 13:02:05','2020-06-29 16:02:05','',87,'http://localhost/index.php/2020/06/29/87-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(90,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:50','2020-06-29 16:02:50','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the findings of a new study are to be believed, the novel coronavirus holding the world hostage at the moment poses a greater threat to the health of humans, animals and plants than previously suspected. The study – which still awaits peer-review –&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.news-medical.net/news/20200622/Dire-warning-on-contamination-of-water-and-COVID-19-spread.aspx\">suggests</a>&nbsp;that Covid-19 is able to remain stable in contaminated water for up to 25 days, and places a special focus on contamination through sewage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even though these findings still need final verification, they nonetheless bring attention to the potentially great risk for infection from dirty water at a time when personal hygiene is of the essence. The sewage systems in Southeast Asia’s urban centers are often inadequate, with wastewater being pumped into rivers and the ocean, where diseases can potentially become endemic within flora and fauna and thus, when consumed, act as a new vector for the coronavirus to affect human health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Dirty flow: The Covid-19 risk in Southeast Asia’s rivers','','publish','open','open','','dirty-flow-the-covid-19-risk-in-southeast-asias-rivers','','','2020-06-30 11:09:51','2020-06-30 14:09:51','',0,'http://localhost/?p=90',0,'post','',0),(91,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:46','2020-06-29 16:02:46','','4951944214_b111404211_k','','inherit','open','closed','','4951944214_b111404211_k','','','2020-06-29 13:02:46','2020-06-29 16:02:46','',90,'http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/4951944214_b111404211_k.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(92,1,'2020-06-29 13:02:50','2020-06-29 16:02:50','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the findings of a new study are to be believed, the novel coronavirus holding the world hostage at the moment poses a greater threat to the health of humans, animals and plants than previously suspected. The study – which still awaits peer-review –&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.news-medical.net/news/20200622/Dire-warning-on-contamination-of-water-and-COVID-19-spread.aspx\">suggests</a>&nbsp;that Covid-19 is able to remain stable in contaminated water for up to 25 days, and places a special focus on contamination through sewage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even though these findings still need final verification, they nonetheless bring attention to the potentially great risk for infection from dirty water at a time when personal hygiene is of the essence. The sewage systems in Southeast Asia’s urban centers are often inadequate, with wastewater being pumped into rivers and the ocean, where diseases can potentially become endemic within flora and fauna and thus, when consumed, act as a new vector for the coronavirus to affect human health.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','Dirty flow: The Covid-19 risk in