e lifeblood of an American culture of speed, convenience, and disposability that’s conquered the globe. Plastic contains our hot coffee and frozen dinners. It is the material of childhood, from Pampers to Playmobil to PlayStation 4. It cloaks our e-commerce purchases and is woven into our sneakers, fast fashion, and business fleece. Humans are now using a million plastic bottles a minute, and 500 billion plastic bags a year — including those we use to bag up our plastic-laden trash.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But the world’s plastic waste is not so easily contained. Massive quantities of this forever material are spilling into the oceans — the equivalent of a dump-truck load every minute. Plastic is also fouling our mountains, our farmland, and spiraling into an unmitigatable environmental disaster. John Hocevar is a marine biologist who leads the Oceans Campaign for Greenpeace, and spearheaded the group’s response to the BP oil spill in the Gulf. Increasingly, his work has centered on plastics. “This is a much bigger problem than ‘just’ an ocean issue, or even a pollution issue,” he says. “We’ve found plastic everywhere we’ve ever looked. It’s in the Arctic and the Antarctic and in the middle of the Pacific. It’s in the Pyrenees and in the Rockies. It’s settling out of the air. It’s raining down on us.”<br></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><strong>The worst of our global plastics</strong> map</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>ALSO IN THIS REGION</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:newspack-blocks/homepage-articles {\"className\":\"is-style-default\",\"showExcerpt\":false,\"showAuthor\":false,\"postLayout\":\"grid\",\"typeScale\":2} /-->\n\n<!-- wp:group {\"customBackgroundColor\":\"#f5f5f5\",\"align\":\"full\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignfull has-background\" style=\"background-color:#f5f5f5\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\"><!-- wp:heading {\"align\":\"center\",\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"has-text-align-center\">Título da galeria em H3</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[485,488,491,494,478,475,472,375,381,215,201,205],\"columns\":4} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-4 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pasifik4a.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"485\" data-full-url=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pasifik4a.jpg\" data-link=\"http://localhost/index.php/2020/07/07/bill-to-end-palaus-26-year-fishing-ban-on-endangered-species-faces-pushback/pasifik4a/\" class=\"wp-image-485\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pasifika5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"488\" data-full-url=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pasifika5.jpg\" data-link=\"http://localhost/index.php/2020/07/07/tuvalu-wields-new-data-in-the-fight-against-climate-change/pasifika5/\" class=\"wp-image-488\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pasifikafeat.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"491\" data-full-url=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pasifikafeat.jpg\" data-link=\"http://localhost/index.php/2020/07/07/atoll-nations-declare-their-rights-to-remain-in-their-islands/pasifikafeat/\" class=\"wp-image-491\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pasifik6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"494\" data-full-url=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pasifik6.jpg\" data-link=\"http://localhost/index.php/2020/07/07/tuvalu-wields-new-data-in-the-fight-against-climate-change/pasifik6/\" class=\"wp-image-494\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"http://localhost/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/pasifika3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"478\" data-full-url=\"http://localhost/wp-content/upl